dec

VarTypeNative dec(java.lang.String decExpr,
                  java.lang.String[] importList)
Declares the native variable type defined in the specified expression string.

An expression string is based on native type expressions adding info about how this type is addressed as a variable (field member of a structure, a formal method parameter...).

"By pointer" and "by value" conventionalisms are specified with the presence or absence of '*' character in the end of a native type expression.

Anyway, some types are ever "by pointer" and is not necessary to specify the '*' character. See VarTypeNative.getVarConv() for a complete list.

Used ClassLoader, parameter importList using, spacing etc is the same as explained in NativeTypeManager.dec(String,String[]).

Expression examples:

"int *"

Declares an int pointer. Is equivalent to: "com.innowhere.jnieasy.core.data.NativeInteger"
"mypkg.MyStructure"

Declares the user defined mypkg.MyStructure class by value.
"mypkg.MyStructure *"

Declares the user defined mypkg.MyStructure class by pointer.
"mypkg.MyStructure **"

Declares a pointer to a pointer to mypkg.MyStructure elements. Is equivalent to: Pointer.class.getName() + "{mypkg.MyStructure*}"
"mypkg.MyStructure*[3]"

Declares an array of 3 pointers to mypkg.MyStructure elements, the array is defined by value.
"mypkg.MyStructure[3]*"

Declares an array of 3 elements of mypkg.MyStructure by value, the array is defined by pointer.
"String"

Declares an ANSI java.lang.String native variable type by pointer.

Parameters:
decExpr - the expression string defining the native variable type.
importList - the included list of classes using Java import syntax. Can be null.
Returns:
the native variable type of the declaration.
See Also:
NativeTypeManager.dec(String,String[]), dec(Class,int), VarTypeNative.getDeclarationString()

dec

VarTypeNative dec(java.lang.Class clasz,
                  int varConv)
Declares the default native variable type of the specified class using the specified variable conventionalism.

This method relies on NativeTypeManager.dec(Class) to get the default native type declaration of the specified class and TypeNative.decVarType(int) to declare the native variable type.

Current implementation is:

return getTypeManager().dec(clasz).decVarType(varConv);

Parameters:
clasz - the class to declare.
varConv - the variable conventionalism.
Returns:
the native variable type of the class.
See Also:
dec(TypeNative,int)

dec

VarTypeNative dec(java.lang.Class clasz)
Declares the default native variable type of the specified class using the default variable conventionalism of the type.

This method relies on NativeTypeManager.dec(Class) to get the default native type declaration of the specified class and TypeNative.decVarType() to declare the native variable type.

Current implementation is:

return getTypeManager().dec(clasz).decVarType();

Parameters:
clasz - the class to declare.
Returns:

dec

VarTypeNative dec(TypeNative typeDec,
                  int varConv)
Declares the native variable type of the specified native type using the specified variable conventionalism.

This method relies on TypeNative.decVarType(int) to declare the native variable type.

Current implementation is:

return typeDec.decVarType(varConv);

Parameters:
typeDec - the native type base to declare the native variable type.
varConv - the variable conventionalism.
Returns:
the native variable type of the class.
